The paper proposes an unsupervised method for learning universal embeddings of time series, which is a problem related to machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The method uses causal dilated convolutions, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) tasks. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of a triplet loss, which is a common technique in neural network optimization (cs.NE).
